  <summary date="2005-06-28T19:44:04Z" status="Introduced in House">Up-Skilling Tax Credit Act of 2005 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow a general business tax credit for up to 20 percent of the cost of technical training for employees performing services in a trade or business of the taxpayer. Limits the amount of the credit to $1,000 for each employee, reduced by credit amounts for all prior taxable years. Terminates the credit after 2009.</summary>
